title: Viral Cash Me Outside girl Danielle Bregoli cashing in on fame with merchandise line - Yahoo7
text:
Share Viral Cash Me Outside girl Danielle Bregoli cashing in on fame with merchandise line - Yahoo7 An out-of-control teen dubbed the "Cash Me Outside" Girl, who made headlines after an expletive-ridden appearance on US television show Dr Phil, has cashed in on her instant fame by launching her own merchandise range. Close 'Cash me ousside' girl to make her TV return UP NEXT VIDEO 'Cash me ousside' girl to make her TV return. 'Cash me ousside' girl to make her TV return 
Danielle Bregoli ,13, rose to fame last year when her mother asked Dr Phil for help fixing her daughter's "car-stealing, knife-wielding" ways, during an intervention on his reality TV show. 
During the segment, the out-of-control teen invited members of the audience to "cash me ousside, how bow dah", which her mother translated to, "meet her outside" to fight, "how about that?". Her initial appearance on Dr Phil went viral when she tried to fight members of the audience. Source: Dr Phil 
Following the show, the loose-cannon became a social media sensation and currently has 3.3 million Instagram followers, and more than 9,200 on Twitter. 
Her merchandise line , developed in collaboration with Los Angeles-based design brand PizzaSlime, is the next stage of Bregoli's viral assault. 'She got her a** whooped by 13-year-old': Cash me outside teen explains plane brawl Danielle Bregoli can be seen screaming in another passenger's face as a brawl erupted on a Spirit Airlines flight on Monday. Pictures: Instagram 
The "CASH ME OUSSIDE HOW BOW DAH" Collection, listed as "Official as f**k", features T-shirts and hoodies printed with Bregoli's iconic catchphrases, as well as tote bags and other accessories with the teen's face on them. 
A tee will set you back $US30 and hoodies are priced at $US65, but those looking to throw $US250 around can nab a “woven photo blanket” featuring the young girl's face, described as “great after a bath, when watching a movie at night or for sleeping”. 
The product descriptions on each item include phrases like: "Only for bhad bhabies!", "Do not buy this if you a ho", "B***h you wish you was me!" and "Yup, I'm the bhaddest b***h on the planet." The viral sensation has launched a merch range including 'official as f**k' T-shirts, hoodies, and other accessories. Picture: Instagram She announced there would be a second appearance on Dr Phil. Source: Facebook 
Bregoli made headlines earlier this week when she was kicked off a Spirit Airlines flight on Monday after she reportedly punched another passenger while boarding the LAX bound aircraft. 
Joined by her mother, the teen was on her flying back to Los Angeles to film a reunion with Dr Phil when the fight broke out. 
The teen was filmed hurling punches and screaming at a female passenger before landing a large blow on her opponent, adding to her growing list of viral videos. 
The Dr Phil segment is expected to go to air on Friday in the US. Close 'Cash me outside' teen explains flight incident UP NEXT
